Last updated: 01 October 2025

Bondi is committed to protecting minors and preventing child sexual abuse and exploitation (CSAE).
We maintain strict policies, proactive detection mechanisms, and a zero-tolerance approach toward harmful behavior.


---

1. No Minors Allowed

Bondi is strictly for users 18 years and older.

We do not knowingly permit anyone under 18 to access the service.

Accounts suspected of belonging to minors are immediately suspended and investigated.

Verified underage accounts are deleted permanently.



---

2. Zero-Tolerance Policy for Child Sexual Abuse and Exploitation (CSAE)

Bondi strictly prohibits:

Sexual content involving minors

Grooming, coercion, or predatory behavior

Requesting or sharing explicit images of minors

Attempting to contact minors for romantic or sexual purposes

Any depiction or suggestion of child exploitation


Violations result in:

Immediate permanent account ban

Preservation of evidence

Mandatory reporting to relevant authorities

Cooperation with law enforcement investigations



---

3. In-App Reporting Tools

Users can report:

Suspected minors

Harmful or abusive behavior

Inappropriate photos

CSAE-related concerns


These reports are reviewed by Bondiâ€™s safety team. Urgent issues are escalated immediately.


---

4. Moderation & Enforcement

Bondi uses:

Selfie verification to reduce fake or underage accounts

Automated systems to detect suspicious behavior

Manual review by trained moderators

Immediate removal of illegal or harmful content


We continually improve our detection mechanisms to maintain a safe environment.


---

5. Cooperation With Law Enforcement

Bondi complies with:

Local and international laws on child safety

Mandatory CSAE reporting requirements

Requests from national and regional authorities


When required, we:

Preserve evidence under legal guidelines

Provide information to law enforcement agencies

Support investigations into CSAE cases



---

6. How to Report CSAE Concerns

If you believe a user poses a risk to minors or is engaging in CSAE-related behavior, report them immediately using the in-app reporting tools.

For urgent or serious issues, you may also contact us directly:

